726074f-b.text:
34-11 to 34-19 Astoria Boulevard, north side, between 34th and 35th Streets. The frame house is no. 34-11 and 34-15. These, as well as other buildings on the north side of the Boulevard, were later torn down for the construction of the Grand Central Parkway approach
to the Triborough Bridge.
View 2 shows the same group of buildings being torn down, seen
from 35th Street.
View 1: March 11, 1931
View 2: September 20, 1934
P.L. Snerr
E.S. Loulan
